article.linkText: Brown scores 20 as Saint Joseph's knocks off American 69-53
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Xzayvier Brown scored 20 points as Saint Joseph's beat American 69-53 on Wednesday night. Brown shot 6 for 9 (4 for 7 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line for the Hawks (7-2). Erik Reynolds II scored 14 points while shooting 6 for 12, including 2 for 6 from beyond the arc, and added six rebounds and five assists. Rasheer Fleming had 13 points and was 6 of 9 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range). The Eagles (4-6) were led in scoring by Elijah Stephens, who finished with 16 points and four assists. Matt Rogers added 12 points for American. NEXT UP Saint Joseph's plays Sunday against Princeton at home, and American visits VMI on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
